<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-591] Log4j closes MongoDB connections after the first log message</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-591</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It seems that the AbstractDatabaseManager behavior is now to close the connection after the buffer is flushed (or immediately after a write if there is no buffer). These are the calls to commitAndClose().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The intended behavior for close() is that it would return a connection to the connection pool. That would make sense for most good database drivers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the MongoDBProvider simply closes the MongoClient, releasing the entire pool. This means that further attempts to write to the log, after the first time, will fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
